getAddress(string).notice: Retrieves the address associated with a given name.

setAddress(string,address).notice: Changes the address associated with a particular name.

AddressSet(string,address,address).notice: Emitted when an address is modified in the registry.

userdoc.notice: AddressManager is a legacy contract that was used in the old version of the Optimism         system to manage a registry of string names to addresses. We now use a more standard         proxy system instead, but this contract is still necessary for backwards compatibility         with several older contracts.
